{"title": "Making of an American", "description": "Jacob Riis was an esteemed reporter and documentary photographer in New York City. In his autobiography he movingly recounts his early life and unrelenting attempts at courtship in Denmark followed by his later experiences in the United States, first as a struggling itinerant immigrant and later as a journalist. He describes how he became a reporter and how his work in lower Manhattan\u2019s teeming, squalid immigrant communities sparked his passion and activism for social reform. In his opening note he writes: \u201cTo those who have been asking if they are made-up stories, let me say here that they are not.\u201d\n\nNOTE: Elizabeth's letter (In Chapter 7) is read by Ann Boulais. \u2013 Lee Smalley", "duration": 35948, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1714", "name": "Jacob A. Riis"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/making_of_an_american_ls_1606_librivox/makingamerican_1607.jpg", "copyright_year": "1901", "genres": ["Biography & Autobiography"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Lee Smalley"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Lee Smalley"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Laura Victoria"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Meeting On The Long Bridge", "readers": [8138], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/making_of_an_american_ls_1606_librivox/makingofanamerican_01_riis_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2631}, {"section": 2, "title": "I Land In New York And Take A Hand In The Game", "readers": [8138], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/making_of_an_american_ls_1606_librivox/makingofanamerican_02_riis_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1904}, {"section": 3, "title": "I Go To War At Last, And Sow The Seed Of Future Campaigns", "readers": [8138], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/making_of_an_american_ls_1606_librivox/makingofanamerican_03_riis_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1621}, {"section": 4, "title": "Working And Wandering"